Operators:-
    Symbol that tell compiler to perform some operations

Tyeps of Operators:

1. Arithmatic Operators:
 a. Binary Operators:-
    +, -, *, /, %.
 
 b. Unary Operators:
    ++, --

2. Increment Operators:-
 a. Pre increment:-
    ++a 

 b. Post increment:-
    a++ 

 c. Post decrement:-
    a--

 d. Pre decrement:-
    --a 

3. Relational Operators:
    == :- Equal to
    != :- Not Equal to
    > :- Greater than 
    < :- less than
    >= :- Greater than eual to
    <= :- less than equal to

4. Logical Operators:- 
    && :- Logical AND :-
        If statement 1 and Statement 2 Both are true then
        result will be True, Otherwise the result will be False

    || :- Logical OR :-
        If the statement 1 and statement 2 both are False then
        the result will be False, Otherwise the result will be True

    ! :- Logical NOT :-
        If the statement is True it will become False,
        If the statement is False it will become True.

5. Bitwise Operators:-

    & = Binary AND
    | = Binary OR
    ^ = Binary XOR (Similar Values :- Flase / 0, Different Values :- True / 1)
    ~ = Binary one's complement (Convertors 1 to 0, and 0 to 1)
    << = Binary left Shift :- 
        ex :
            A = 0101
            A<<1
            result = 1010

    >> == Binary Right Shift :-
        ex :
            A = 0101
            A>>1
            result = 0010

